item.title: My compile dont work please help
item.dc:creator: @Tom Tom
item.description:
@Tom wrote:

Put your compiler with the Java files, or it has nothing to compile.

EDIT: Okay, seen as thought you asked me to explain easier, a compile compilers Java files into .class files.

Basically when you hit compile it makes all the text in .java into a .class file + Java byte code.

Your server runs on the .class not the Java.

Basically for it to make a change you need to c & p your compiler into the place where Java files for that source are located, it will then make them into .class which your server will read from.

Sometimes servers have a BIN which .class are located at.
